itemListElement.name: San Juan Island Whale Watching & Friday Harbor Day Trip from Seattle

name: San Juan Island Whale Watching & Friday Harbor Day Trip from Seattle
description:
Enjoy whale watching and a San Juan Island day trip from Seattle! This is the only cruise that leaves directly from downtown Seattle, allowing you to skip the traffic and get out on the water. With the guidance of a trained onboard naturalist, you will be taken to an area world-renowned for wildlife, where you will be on the lookout for orca, minke and humpback whales as well as Dallâ€™s porpoise, seals, otters, bald eagles and more! Afterwards, you will have a stopover in Friday Harbor for a chance to grab a bite to eat or explore.

Daily Schedule:

8:15 AM: Depart Pier 69 in Seattle

12:00 PM: Arrive Friday Harbor (if you are going whale watching, you stay on the boat)

12:15 PM to 2:45 PM: Whale & Sealife Search

2:45 PM to 5:00 PM: Free time in Friday Harbor

5:15 PM: Depart Friday Harbor

8:00 PM: Arrive Seattle

review.name: Whale watching tour
review.reviewBody: We booked a whale watching tour and on the day of the tour we got told that the weather was not favorable and if we want to reschedule we could. Come to find out they would take 50% of our paid fare and the refund for 2 people who went and didnt get to go on the whale tour was $23 ( what a joke, especially we asked numerous times the sales person at their ticket booth about there refund policy) So we went anyway and the team was nice on the boat. They dropped as off for 4 hr at Friday Harbor with nothing to do and most of the stores closed for the season and all the tours were booked. Not impressed with the customer service we got from this company. Also the weather was sunny and easy going. We felt ripped off and will never recommend this company to anyone.

review.name: A whale of an adventure
review.reviewBody:
After spending days sightseeing in the city of Seattle, we were looking for a more "natural" type of Seattle adventure.  This 12 hour trip was just that.  After spending about 4 hours on their ferry we reached San Juan Island where many people disembarked.  Then we were off for our 2 1/2 hour whale watching adventure.  We first saw a hump back whale, and in the next few hours saw 9 killer whales, and one baby calf.  At oone point four of the whales were all in line shooting their spray up in to the air, and from my viewpoint, it was as if they were putting on a show for us!    The whales appeared over and over again.  We couldn't have been happier.

We saw a bald eagle, sea lions, porpoises, and many other creatures native to this area.

When we returned to San Juan Island for our 2 1/2 hour land break, we were greeted with a parade put on by local farmers.   Some of the farmers were tossing out candies while others handed out candy.  One child who appeared to be about 5 years old was walking the parade route carrying a live chicken.   This parade was not like the kind of parade I am used to seeing in NYC.  It's simplicity was magical, as was the rest of the day!

Lastly, the naturalist onboard our ferry, Lauren, was amazing.  Her love of the whales and her job was obvious from start to finish.  

I only hope that if you go on this tour, you are as lucky as we were!

review.name: Terrible experience
review.reviewBody: We saw no whales.  We only got to spend an hour in San Juan because the crew altered the trip because there were no whales.  We saw no other boats on the water.  We were told that they had seen whales every day since March with three exceptions.  We spent 20 minutes watching deer on the side of the hill.  I convinced my husband to go on this cruise.  It was the final day of our trip and this was supposed to be the grand finale.  Horrible experience.

review.name: Whale watching
review.reviewBody: This was sold to us as a whale watching trip. What a joke this was! If you want to go whale watching this is not company to do it with. It was a regular ferry to San Juan from Seattle, with a stop over of several hours, it seems they have discovered a way of making more money out of their customers by, advertising as whale watching. The ferry drops customers at San Juan then heads out into the bay, for brief search for whales, as the ferry was so large we were also restricted as to how close we could get to the whales. After about 30 mins, and a brief sighting, of 1 whale tail. We headed back to San Juan, for a hour half stop over, pleasant town. The advertised whale watching was a joke. Trip took over 12 hours, complete waste of 1 of our precious days in Seattle. If you want to whale watching choose another company.

review.name: BEST EXPERIENCE EVER
review.reviewBody: If you can spare the 12 hours, you should definitely check off a bucket list item and go on this tour. The staff is very friendly and knowledgeable. The ship was clean and well taken care of . If I had only one thing I would say is that I wish we had more time on the island . We wanted to find whales so that limited our island experience. Other than that, it was an amazing experience and I would highly encourage anyone to go on this.

review.name: Nice Day Out
review.reviewBody: I went on this excursion by myself while my husband was in Seattle on business. I am prone to motion sickness, but wore sea bands and was fine. This day was really more about the trip than the destination.  I sat outside on the top level, yes it was cold, but I didnt come on the boat to sit in a "fish bowl" and look out a window.  When we saw the whales, they were far away and hard to see with so many passengers trying to take photos. I also could do without the 2 hour layover and would have rather headed back. All in all I enjoyed the day, the ride and the people I met, but if you're wanting to see whales close up, you will be disappointed.

review.name: A very long day
review.reviewBody: The ship leaves Seattle at 8:15 a.m. and travels to Friday Harbor, which is a 3 hour ride.  Along the way there really is nothing to look at as far as seals, or sea lions....and definitely no whales.  We dropped off some people at Friday Harbor and then left to find whales...they explain that there is no guarantee....and it is strictly done by communication with others in the area.  We did see the tops of whales...not a whole whale...and we had to stay so far away from them the event that we had all been looking forward to was really a let down.  Then we went back to Friday Harbor, which was super cute and very nice.  Again, back on the boat for another 3 hour ride back to Seattle.  The weather was beautiful and we did see a couple of dolphins...this trip is extremely high for what you get.  The ship is comfortable, however, the food selection while good was limited and they ran out of some of the favorite items.  No effort in Friday Harbor was made to replenish the food for the ride back to Seattle.  So, if you do not purchase food in Friday Harbor or bring some onboard, you will be hungry because you arrive back in Seattle at 8 p.m.  If you have an Uber account, you will need to call an Uber to come and get you at the waterfront.  We found two taxis but they were down a ways from the docking point.  Buses don't run at the waterfront after 8 p.m. The Pike Place Market was also closed.  So, plan accordingly.  Also, a note to parents, please do not bring chldren on this cruise that are under 10.....the cruise is very long....even for adults.  And, we had a baby on the cruise, who screamed and cried the entire cruise.....dampening the mood for everyone.  Would definitely hope that parents would realize being on a boat for 10 hours is alot to ask for kids.  Would not book this cruise again.  A whale watching cruise usually includes sitings of whales.....not just fins and blow holes.....was hoping to see whales.  The staff was extraordinary and did a great job!

review.name: Whale Watchin, not Watching Whales
review.reviewBody: Ship is comfortable with acceptable food and beverage offerings. Staff did a good job but only saw 1 gray whale. Saw a few seals, couple of otters and a couple of porpoises most of which were a good distance away. Friday harbor is a great stop in the afternoon before returning to Seattle.

review.name: Long Day - Not my Fav Whale Watch
review.reviewBody:
We have had the opportunity to go on several whale watches (California, Cabo, New England). This trip just did not match those other experiences. The trip out and back is very long. Seating onboard is cramped and uncomfortable, except for the upper deck. Positives: scenery, knowledgeable guide, convenient, Orcas! 

I would opt for driving to other departure points where local companies offer smaller boats and a more intimate experience.

review.name: Great trip!
review.reviewBody: This was a great trip! We did see orcas as promised! The crew was good at communicating with other ships in the area to find the pods of whales. It is quite a long day: we left at 8:15 a.m  & returned at 8 pm. I believe it is the only whale watching tour out of Seattle. A few tips: get a seat inside as we were outside on top of the boat all day. (A bit too much wind). The people inside weren't very willing to make room for us.ðŸ˜¬ Also, the online info said to arrive 1 hour early to check in (7:15 a m.). No way! When we arrived that early, they told us to go get a coffee & come back in ~ 30 minutes! ðŸ˜². Otherwise, we did really love the trip. The stop on San Juan Island was nice. Enjoyed the Whale museum & ordered dinner to go from a restaurant near the harbor.

itemListElement.name: Seattle to Victoria Day Trip with Royal BC Museum

name: Seattle to Victoria Day Trip with Royal BC Museum
description: Soak in Victoriaâ€™s rich history and culture at British Columbiaâ€™s premier museum with a quick and easy day trip from downtown Seattle on our high-speed Victoria Clipper catamaran. Discover impressive First Nationâ€™s art as well as aÂ variety of fun interactive exhibits that allow you to get a peek at the flora and fauna of BCâ€™s coastal rainforests or wander through a collection of life-sized totem poles. If you are a history buff, this is an experience you wonâ€™t forget!

name: WASHINGTON ST AGRICULTURE, Apples & Irrigation
description:
You will be amazed at the variety of landscapes and terrain you will see in one day in Washington. Orchards with fruit of the season: Apples, cherries, apricots, and pears. You'll see wheat fields and vineyards, potatoes, and hops.

Then you'll see a fascinating landscape; a huge dry waterfall and deep canyon, and drive into the canyon. Stop and feel the minerals in Soap Lake and the heat of the semi-arid climate on this wonderous experience if sights and scenes.

name: Gondola Ride to Mt Rainier
description: The beautiful mountain drive is enough to merit this trip, but then the gondola at Crystal Mountain takes you to the top ridge with a remarkable view of all 5 of Washington's volcanoes. Mount Rainier being a rocks throw away, it's incredible from this viewpoint. Restaurant at the Summit if you wish to buy lunch or beverages.

review.name: Great Personalized Experience
review.reviewBody: Cheryl picked us up promptly at our hotel in downtown Seattle. The SUV was clean and we were provided with snacks and water bottles for the trip to Crystal Mountain. Cheryl was a wonderful guide who provided us with a lot of interesting history and information about the area on the way to and from the mountain. It was a refreshing change of pace from the larger group tours we have taken in the past because we were able to have a real conversation with the tour guide. It felt like we were spending the day with an old friend or family member who has lived in the area for a long time. The gondola ride to the top of Crystal Mountain was relaxing, and we had great views of the surrounding mountains with our lunch. We were not rushed at all and had ample time to enjoy the wonderful views of Mt. Rainier, which was clearly visible on the day we visited. For those wanting a change of pace from the "standard" tour format, I would highly recommend this tour!

itemListElement.name: Wine Tasting, Vineyards in Eastern WA from Seattle

name: Wine Tasting, Vineyards in Eastern WA from Seattle
description:
Wine Tasting, in the vineyards. Head over the mountains into Eastern Washington, leaving the rainy coastal climate of Seattle for the sun-drenched desert hills of the Yakima and Columbia valleys. You'll see lush evergreen forests and semi-arid sagebrush on this interesting travel route to the wine country.

Your guide will pick you up at your agreed upon location and head east toward the Cascades. Sample wines from each of 3 wineries, noting the differences in each glass by the area's distinctive features, from soil and terrain to sun exposure and rainfall.

You may pick 2 wineries in the area (not too far out of the way), or we have some pre-set ones that are popular. 

Stop along the way to complement your tastings with a tasty lunch, or enjoy the food offerings at the wineries.

review.name: Great Wine Tasting & Washington State Experience
review.reviewBody: Cheryl planned a great day of wine tasting for us and planned little extra touches that made even the trip from our Seattle hotel to the vineyards/wineries and back an enjoyable experience.  She called us ahead to customize the trip per our preferences, she  pointed out highlights along the way after picking us up from our hotel, and made sure we had snacks, water (and water bottle to keep), and tailored lunch across a couple of the wineries per our preference, all in addition to the wine tasting experiences at three wineries that had a great diversity and delicious wines.  Besides the wine tasting, the trip back and forth from Seattle was a great part of the experience as we really enjoyed the scenery and learning a little about the different Washington  landscapes and climates between Seattle and Eastern Washington (desert area).

review.name: Canceled on us THE DAY BEFORE OUR TOUR!
review.reviewBody: Booked the VIP Ultimate Seattle Food Tour for 6 people on January 6th for March 18th.  I was notified that our host was being briefed on March 3rd and I was contacted by March 4th.  Details were exchanged and a proposed itinerary was received on March 15th.  We paid $976 for this 4 hour tour and I was told that our "budget" for food for the 6 of us was $213.  The itinerary included 3 stops where we were expected to order off the menu and share.  Transportation between restaurants was not included.  I asked our host what their recommendations were (why those particular restaurants were selected) and commented that making 3 reservations, being responsible for our own transportation, and ordering off the menu/sharing was something we could have just done on our own.  On the morning of March 17th - ONE DAY BEFORE OUR TOUR - I received notification that our tour was canceled "due to COVID" (which isn't being honest, IMO).  What horrible service.

itemListElement.name: Wine Passport: Self-Guided Wine Tasting in Seattle and Woodinville

name: Wine Passport: Self-Guided Wine Tasting in Seattle and Woodinville
description:
Seattleâ€™s favorite self-guided wine tasting passport! Explore and sip at 10 different Seattle area wineries of your choice. Let Lyft get you there, as each Wine Passport comes with $50.00 in Lyft ride credit. 

Choose from over 25 participating wineries in Seattle and Woodinville.Â  

This self-guided tasting experience is curated by you on your mobile phone. The price includes 10 tastings valid for 1 year from the date of purchase. Visit participating wineries anytime they are open to the public to redeem your tasting.

review.name: So worth it
review.reviewBody: This is so worthwhile! We used Lyft from downtown Seattle to Woodinville ($40 ride) and then you can walk between the wineries because they are so close together. My husband and I each had a passport and everyone readily accepted it. We only made it to 3 vineyards but had we gone without the passport the tastings alone wouldâ€™ve cost us more than the passport did.

review.name: Best Day Drinking Wine!
review.reviewBody:
This review is for the Wine Passport - We visited Seattle for a weekend and got the wine passport to go wine tasting as it seemed like a great deal, and we LOVE wine!  For $60 you get 10 wine tastings (your choice from 25+ wineries around the seattle area) and $50 in Lyft credit (5 rides, $10 off each ride).  The Wine Passport was very user friendly - you just download the app and select the 10 wineries you would like to visit.  When you arrive at the winery, you hit "redeem" and show it to the person pouring wine.  9 of the 10 wineries we visited knew about the app and there were no issues redeeming.  The one who didnt know about it, just said ok and gave us our tasting.  :)  

The wineries in Woodenville were awesome! Some were smaller and close together, and others were larger and far apart.  You can walk between a lot of them!  Our favorite winery we visited was Novelty Hill Januik - they had a huge wine list and you could select any 6 wines to sample!  Also, you do not have to use all the tastings in the same day, you can spread them out over a weekend or longer.  Same with the lyft rides. 

If your visiting Seattle, or if you live in Seattle, you have got to try the Wine Passport!  Not only is it a great deal, its a great time with friends, drinking great wine!

name: Hands on Sushi Rolls class
description:
Weâ€™ll meet atÂ a private cooking class kitchen, prune kitchen Seattle, in a residential neighborhood. Fumiko will give the guests a hands-on Sushi making lesson including how to make Sushi rice.Â  After she demonstrates step by step instructions of how to create Sushi rolls, you will roll 3 Sushi rolls(Cucumber roll, Salmon roll, and a half Futo maki) and plate your Sushi rolls with your own design.Â You will devour your own creations. 
 Ingredients include Fresh Tuna, fresh salmon, avocado, shrimp, cucumber, fish roe, cream cheese and Imitation crab.

review.name: Canâ€™t wait to make sushi at home!
review.reviewBody: We truly enjoyed the sushi making class. Fumiko was an excellent teacher! She had a very clean and well organized kitchen, offered tea as well as Japanese candies, and all of the sushi making experience needed to educate some beginners! The walk to the fish market was lovely, Fumiko shared her knowledge of the history of the area. The fish market was clean and had all the tools required to make sushi at home. The sushi instructions were easy to follow and more importantly, delicious! A great way to spend the late morning with my boyfriend and brother and his girlfriend. The small size of the class ensured everyone got to know one another and made it more fun! Highly recommend.

review.name: Sushi class
review.reviewBody: I had a great experience learning how to make sushi today! I highly recommend giving this class a try. Fumiko was very friendly and great at explaining the history of sushi. If Iâ€™m ever in Seattle I would do this again.

review.name: Super Sushi Class
review.reviewBody: My favorite Christmas present. Super informative class with an approachable entry into making your own sushi. Iâ€™ve loved sushi, and have been afraid to make it myself, for a long time. No more! From the rice, to buying fish, to making rollsâ€¦this class gave me confidence to do it at home.

review.name: Fabulous!
review.reviewBody: Our group had a wonderful time learning all the tricks to making a delicious sushi tray.  The instructor had a way of not only making the class informative but fun as well.  Highly recommend this class for all sushi enthusiasts.

itemListElement.name: Sailing Adventure on the Puget Sound

name: Sailing Adventure on the Puget Sound
description:
Your adventure begins as we embark from the Shilshole Bay Marina, preparing to set sail as we round the break water. Throughout thisÂ 3 hour sailing adventureÂ you'll have an opportunity to learn how to sail, or just let us do the work and enjoy experiencing:
 â€¢ The cool ocean breeze.
 â€¢ Spectacular views of theÂ Olympic Mountains, Downtown Seattle, The Space needle, The Great Wheel, Mount Rainier, Large yachts and massive Merchant Marine Containerships.
 â€¢ WildÂ life such asÂ seals, sea lions, small porpoises, jumping fish and on rare, lucky occasions, Southern Resident Orcas and Humpback whales
 â€¢ Adventure with personalized service and stories in a small group setting

Sit back, relax and enjoy all the amazing views of Seattle and discover what makes the Northwest so special.

review.name: Perfect Day on Puget Sound
review.reviewBody: Would 100/100 times recommend this to anyone with a free afternoon in Seattle.  Having been out on Lake Union multiple times before, while visiting the area, it was an amazing adventure to get out on the Sound especially in a sailboat.  To top it all off, Captain Russ made what was already an amazing experience that much better.  Thanks so much for such a memorable few hours!

review.name: Great Evening on the Water
review.reviewBody: We had a beautiful and relaxing sail on the Puget Sound. How lucky we were to have great weather and a gorgeous view of Mt. Rainier in all its glory. Russ is an delightfully entertaining captain! Definite must do while in Seattle!

itemListElement.name: High-Speed Passenger Ferry From Victoria, British Columbia to Seattle, Washington

name: High-Speed Passenger Ferry From Victoria, British Columbia to Seattle, Washington
description: Take a one-way high-speed passenger ferry from Victoria, British Columbia to Seattle, Washington. Sit back and relax on a scenic 2- to 3-hour cruise as you travel between Canada and the USA. Upgrade and add the round-trip option.

review.name: Stress-free border crossing
review.reviewBody:
The Clipper was a much more attractive, and scenic way to make the crossing from Canada to Seattle without the hassle of airport security.
The Clipper leaves from very close to town, so, you can walk there if needed, even if youâ€™re dragging a suitcase.
Thereâ€™s immigration pre-clearance at check in and again on the other side, but this was the friendliest and easiest crossing weâ€™ve experienced into the USA (and weâ€™re Australians).
We paid for the VIP service â€“ not sure if itâ€™s worth it, but it did give you a dedicated seat upstairs, and free drinks and snacks, as well as priority boarding.
The only downside for us was as the Clipper was departing we were held up for an hour behind cruise ships docking and did not make it to Seattle until very late.
But we enjoyed the simple, stress-free scenic crossing.

review.name: Easy Cruising luxury travel
review.reviewBody: We took the ferry from Victoria to Seattle.  It beats flying. Why?  The check in was easy, luggage taken up to* hours before trip. Customs easy both leaving Canada & entering US. Cabin spacious, seating, leather chairs very comfortable.  Watch the scenery or view  from the rear deck.   Puget Sound is very picturesque.The trip was on time, and wharf is in the heart of Seattle, unlike the airport.  Strongly recommend this trip

itemListElement.name: Sunday Brunch Cruise with Buffet in Washington

name: Sunday Brunch Cruise with Buffet in Washington
description:
Come sailing on Seattleâ€™s Tall Ship, a historic 19th-century style gaff-rigged schooner. We offer three public sailing tours daily from Seattleâ€™s downtown waterfront. Our beautiful sailing ship, the Bay Lady, evokes the romance of traditional sailing as we work together to set the sails, turn off the engine, and sail off into an age of cannon fire and sunsets behind the untouched mountain ranges of the Puget Sound. 

Bay Lady is the largest public sailing vessel in Seattle. With her high railing and comfortable seating, she is the premier boat ride for families. 

Enjoy a drink from our onboard bar and set sail into the perfect day on the water!

review.name: The best brunch sail in Seattle
review.reviewBody: We loved this tour! A group of four of us were on a girls trip from Denver. The food was great, the blackberry mimosas were perfect and the sailboat was so relaxing. Definitely something to do while in Seattle.

review.name: The best boating experience downtown.
review.reviewBody:
Best way to cruise Elliot Bay and enjoy views of the city! The captain and crew are so friendly and helpful. A+ service 
Great food and drinks
Even got to help hoist the sails which was fun! 10/10

review.name: A MUST DO EXPERIENCE WHETHER YOU ARE LOCAL OR VISITING!!
review.reviewBody: Definitely my favorite sailing charter to do in Seattle. I am a  Seattle local and my friends and I go out on the Bay Lady at least a couple times during the summer season. Captain Noah and the entire team go above in beyond in their customer service to ensure everyone has the best time. There are some other sailing tours and they are good too, but service is everything and they truly want you to have the best time on board. Seating is very comfortable and spacious. If you get the chance to book the Sunday brunch cruise, DO IT!!!! I always take friends and family who come to town on this cruise as it really shows Seattle beauty. From downtown skyline's to the Olympic mts. and everything in between, I give this cruise a 12/10.

itemListElement.name: Games and Mocktails in Market Loft

name: Games and Mocktails in Market Loft
description:
Join us up in the Melrose Market Loft surrounded by exposed brick, Douglas fir beams, and dark wood library. We'll be providing a full 'mocktail bar' (cold non-alcoholic beverages), and we'll be popping corn on the stove top. Additionally, you'll have access to a tea lab in the loft where you can custom blend your own cup.

Look forward to finishing off your evening in a relaxing environment with down-to-earth conversation and lighthearted rivalry in a vibrant indoor open air market. To begin with, I will show you around the 'mocktail lab' for you to concoct your own drinks. Then pick your seat at the table. We can have several different activities going on at once, so if the puzzle or a certain game isn't your thing, we'll just round up some extra people and start another! We have a variety of classic board games, playing cards and puzzles. If you have a different game or puzzle in mind, feel free to bring it along to share.

name: Visit Leavenworth on a guided Cascades and Snoqualmie Falls Tour
description:
View the scenic Cascade Mountains and the forest near Deception Falls on your way to the alpine Bavarian village, Leavenworth.
Here you will have time to explore the cozy village before we continue to the majestic Snoqualmie Falls which are 270 feet tall. You will finish the day with a view of Borst Lake where Mount Si is often reflected.
